ame":"Hadoop QA","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2010-03-12T01:51:06.497+0000","updated":"2010-03-12T01:51:06.497+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12458877/comment/12844555","id":"12844555","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=aw","name":"aw","key":"aw","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681"},"displayName":"Allen Wittenauer","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Tijuana"},"body":"For such a simple change, I doubt tests are required. :)","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=aw","name":"aw","key":"aw","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681"},"displayName":"Allen Wittenauer","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Tijuana"},"created":"2010-03-12T16:04:21.859+0000","updated":"2010-03-12T16:04:21.859+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12458877/comment/12844619","id":"12844619","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cutting","name":"cutting","key":"cutting","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Doug Cutting","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Allen, if BASH_SOURCE contains the full path, then can we get rid of the 'bin=`cd \"$bin\"; pwd`' that follows each of these, since the point of that is to get the full path of the bin directory?\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cutting","name":"cutting","key":"cutting","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Doug Cutting","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2010-03-12T19:04:38.021+0000","updated":"2010-03-12T19:04:38.021+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12458877/comment/12844639","id":"12844639","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=aw","name":"aw","key":"aw","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681"},"displayName":"Allen Wittenauer","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Tijuana"},"body":"Actually, I misspoke a bit. It will be full path if it comes from $PATH.  If you call with a relative path, it will contain the relative path.\n\nSo to be more explicit:\n\nif I put this code:\n\n{code}\n#!/bin/bash\necho $BASH_SOURCE\n{code}\n\nin $HOME/bin and make sure $HOME/bin is in my path, you'll see the following:\n\nawittena-mn:bin awittena$ testexec\n/Users/awittena/bin/testexec\n\nawittena-mn:~ awittena$ bin/testexec\nbin/testexec\n\nawittena-mn:~ awittena$ cd bin && testexec\n/Users/awittena/bin/testexec\n\nawittena-mn:~ awittena$ cd bin && ./testexec\n./testexec\n\nSo the cd+pwd combo is still needed, but this should fix the \"in the $PATH\" issue.  It is a shame that bash hid the \"can't find hadoop-config.sh\" error for the past few years.  If you run it with -x set, you'll see it tho.\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=aw","name":"aw","key":"aw","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=aw&avatarId=23681"},"displayName":"Allen Wittenauer","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Tijuana"},"created":"2010-03-12T19:48:27.516+0000","updated":"2010-03-12T19:48:27.516+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12458877/comment/12844667","id":"12844667","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cutting","name":"cutting","key":"cutting","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Doug Cutting","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Sounds reasonable.  Thanks for the explanation.  +1 from me.\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cutting","name":"cutting","key":"cutting","avatarUrls":{"48x